Dialogs.Dialog: By the way...
Manaka
Hmm？ What？
What kinds of TV programs do you usually watch, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
TV？ Why？
You might not watch what other girls like to watch. That's what I think, ▲高嶺＊＊▲.
...I watch what others watch.
I see. I'm sorry. Then you watch variety shows or drama, something like that？
Those things are banned at my house...
Banned！？
My dad doesn't like them. Is this weird？
No... But then do you only watch the news and documentaries？
I also watch other programs like quiz shows and sumo.
(Sumo...？)
Um... Is that weird？
(It's just unexpected...)
By the way...
Manaka
Hmm？ What？
For food, do you have anything you like or dislike in particular？
What I like or dislike in particular？ I don't think there's anything.
I see. But you must've had some when you were a kid, right？ Like how some kids hate mushrooms.
Did I have one...？ Ah, vanilla ice cream！
Vanilla ice cream？ Why？
It came in a large cup, right？ I really loved it. But during grade school...
When I was home alone one day, I just couldn't resist it and ate it all by myself.
You ate the whole cup！？
Yes. And then I got a bad stomach ache and got scolded by Mama. I hated it for a while after that.
I see...
But, it's okay now.
(You are the type that can't control herself, huh, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？)
By the way...
Manaka
Hmm？ What？
Besides tennis, what other sports do you play, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
Sports？ Um, during grade school, I attended swimming class.
Ah, many kids go to swimming class. How well can you swim？
If it's breaststroke, I can keep on swimming forever.
Hah！？ Then I want to watch you swim next time.
Eh？ No... You can't.
Why？
Because it's too embarrassing. When I do breaststroke, I look like a frog...
Is that so...？
By the way...
Manaka
Hmm？ What？
What kind of music do you like, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
Music？ Piano concerto, I guess.
Concer... What？
Um, I love piano tunes. I'm learning piano, too.
Ah, I see. I got it.
...Is it weird？
No, not weird at all. Then how about J-Pop？ Do you listen to such thing？
Of course, I do！
Right！ Which artist do you like？
Eh？ Hmm, that one you see often on TV. That guy with a mustache. The rock guy.
Mustache？ Who's that？
Maybe he already shaved his mustache. It's that guy. You know, right？
(Could it be that she's pretending to know this guy...？)
By the way...
Manaka
Hmm？ What？
Do you have hobbies？ Something besides tennis, ▲高嶺＊＊▲.
Yes. What do you think my hobby is？
Um... Cooking or baking, something like that...
...How did you know？ Is it too common？
No. Many girls like cooking, but I think you would like it too, ▲高嶺＊＊▲.
Really？ Hehe... Since I was a kid, I always quit things halfway, like for classes or sports.
Eh！？
But baking is the only thing I'm really confident with. Next time, I'll let you try it.
Do you have any requests？ Cakes, Japanese sweets, or baked foods？ Anything's fine. Hehe▼
(But she said she always quits halfway through... Will I be okay, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？)
By the way...
Manaka
Hmm？ What？
What are your favorite animals, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
My favorite animals？ I guess rabbits are.
Rabbits？ What do you like about them？
Their tails. They're fluffy, right？ And...
Rabbits are different from dogs or cats. They don't come when I call, but they just appear in front of me and I don't notice.
Hmm？ That's nice, huh？
Yes. They're just so cute. Hehe▼
I see. Then...
And then their mouths look like they're munching something all the time. Such gluttons. Hehe▼
(So your favorite animals are the rabbits then, ▲高嶺＊＊▲...)
By the way...
Manaka
Hmm？ What？
I might have asked you this before, but have to be the successor of your parent's hospital, right ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
I guess...
When I was a child, I wanted to own a bakery shop.
Bakery？
Everyone in a hospital looks so sad, right？ But everyone in a bakery shop looks so happy.
As a child, I always thought that it would be better to be a baker rather than a doctor.
I see... But doctors have such a valuable occupation. I don't think you need me to remind you that.
Of course. Doctors save lives. I know that it's a valuable occupation.
But now... I only want to make someone I love think that he's happy to have me by his side. I just want to make him happy.
I'm such a terrible daughter. I only think about myself.
No, I really admire you for your thoughts. You are such a nice person. That's what I think ▲高嶺＊＊▲.
No, I'm not... But thank you. If you said that, I... No, never mind.
(She wants to make someone she loves happy... I'll also have to be more serious about my future...)
By the way...
Manaka
Hmm？ What？
What are your dreams for your future ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
My dreams and my future are probably totally different.
Eh？
My parents run a hospital, right？ So, I'll have to take care of it. I'm their only child.
So, you'll be a doctor？ I know you can do it, ▲高嶺＊＊▲.
Really？ Why？
Because you're smart, diligent, and gentle to everyone.
I'm not that great of a person. Actually... Actually, I've also been thinking about many bad things.
By the way...
Manaka
Hmm？ What？
Do you have a role model, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
A role model...？ Yeah, Nightingale, I think.
Nightingale... You mean like, "the angel in the white robe"？
Yeah. Not only does she have a kind heart, she is also reasonable and knowledgeable. And she has faith too.
I see... You want to be like her huh, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
I used to... But now, I don't know anymore.
I've just realized that I'm not that special. I'm just an ordinary girl.
By the way...
Manaka
Hmm？ What？
Do you have any role model, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
Yes, many.
I see. Like who？
Um... The closest one to me is my Mama.
Hmm... It's pretty common for all girls, I guess.
Perhaps. But, my Mama is really amazing.
She can cook delicious meals and keep smiling no matter how tired she is. Though sometimes, she would scold me.
Whenever Mama catches a cold and has to rest, my house becomes all gloomy.
I want to become a mother just like my Mama... I guess.
No, what am I saying？ I sound like a little kid now. This is embarrassing.
(I'm sure you can become like your mother, ▲高嶺＊＊▲...)
By the way...
Manaka
Hmm？ What？
Do you have any role models ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
Of course.
I see. Like who？
Long ago, my neighbor opened a bakery. It's that bakery's manager.
That manager went alone to France when she was about our age to pursue her dream.
Wow, that's amazing...
Right？ When I compare myself to her, I don't know if I could do that, or if I even have the courage to do so.
My family would object. And I would have to deal with a language barrier...
It's just so amazing that she knew what she wanted and that she went for it.
I see. She's like the ideal person for you right, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
Yeah, when I baked my first cake, I just imitated her... Now you know my secret...
(Going to France alone？ Could I also do that？ ...Nah, I don't think so...)
By the way...
Manaka
Hmm？ What？
What kinds of movies do you like to watch, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
Movies？ Well... Um...
Do you like historical documentaries or something like that？
...Is that not good？
So I was right, huh？
You're wrong. What I like... No, I can't tell you.
What is it？
Don't laugh, okay？
I won't！
I like Cinderella and Snow White... Those kinds of movies...
With a prince and a princess？
Yeah, because it's really wonderful to see a happy ending...
You're laughing... Geez, I shouldn't have told you！ You liar！
(Sorry...)
By the way...
Manaka
Hmm？ What？
What kinds of novels do you like to read, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
Novels？ Um... I haven't read much lately.
I see. Then how about what you used to read？
I love Sherlock Holmes, and then the Junior Detective League... I used to read a lot of series like that.
You're into mystery and detective novels, huh？
Watson, whatever remains, however improbable, must be the truth.
What？ So, I'm Watson now？
Hehe！ They were really fun. Maybe I'll start reading them again.
(You really enjoy reading mystery novels, huh, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？)
